# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The fundamental operations for strings should be known to solve such questions. LC has different kinds of hard questions. To solve this question one does not need special algorithms or tricks.
But it is  very annoying for debugging until to get right answer!

Maybe solve the easy question first.
[1592. Rearrange Spaces Between Words](https://leetcode.com/problems/rearrange-spaces-between-words/description/)

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Determine which words are in which line.
The function ```print_wIdx``` handles where extra whitespaces to insert.

For 2nd approach, every line is initialized with
```
line = string(maxWidth, ' ');
```
and then the function copy in C++ algorithm is used for copying the ```words[i]``` to the right place; its performance is better than operator+ and beats 100.00% with runtime 0 ms. It is to mention that if operator+ for strings is used, the string line will be allocated several times.

Let's consider the string words=
```["Science","is","what","we","understand","well","enough","to","explain","to","a","computer.","Art","is","everything","else","we","do"]```

Take care where extra whitespaces to insert

