# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
iterate through the input words and form lines that fit within the maximum width.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
The main logic is within the fullJustify function. It iterates through the input words and forms lines that fit within the maximum width. It then uses the addSpaces function to create the justified lines.

The condition for the last line is checked using the isLastLine boolean flag.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity: O(M), M-No of input characteres in a stream
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string addSpaces(vector<string>& words, int maxWidth, int i, int j, bool isLast) {
        string result = words[i];
        if (i == j || isLast) {  // For a single-word line or last line
            for (int k = i + 1; k <= j; ++k) {
                result += " " + words[k];
            }
            result += string(maxWidth - result.length(), ' ');
            return result;
        }

        int totalSpaces = maxWidth - accumulate(words.begin() + i, words.begin() + j + 1, 0, [](int len, const string& word) { return len + word.length(); });
        int slots = j - i;  // Number of slots between words
        int spacesBetweenWords = totalSpaces / slots;
        int extraSpaces = totalSpaces % slots;

        for (int k = i + 1; k <= j; ++k) {
            int spaces = spacesBetweenWords + (extraSpaces-- > 0 ? 1 : 0);
            result += string(spaces, ' ') + words[k];
        }

        return result;
    }

    vector<string> fullJustify(vector<string>& words, int maxWidth) {
        vector<string> result;
        int i = 0, n = words.size();

        while (i < n) {
            int j = i, lineLength = 0;
            while (j < n && lineLength + words[j].length() + (j - i) <= maxWidth) {
                lineLength += words[j].length();
                j++;
            }

            bool isLastLine = (j == n);
            result.push_back(addSpaces(words, maxWidth, i, j - 1, isLastLine));

            i = j;
        }

        return result;
    }
};

```

