solutions.content:
The question seems quite difficult,but when u understand its simple. Basically u have to fit as many words as possible in single line with even spacing between them,if a word dosen't fit it will go to next line.
Refernce Example:
```
words = ["This", "is", "an", "example", "of", "text", "justification."]
maxWidth = 16
```
1. To make this possible we have to do a greedy approach,fit as many words in a line with single space between words, we take single space because if we have words whose toatl length is equal to maxWidth then we cant add spaces and will look like "thisisanexample".
 In above example we can fit "this,is,an",if we try to fit "example" it will exceed maxWidth. So we know first line consits of "this","is","an".
For this line we have to add spaces evenly between words until it reaches maxWidth.
So for `"This","is","an"` should be a string `"This     is    an"` which has length == maxWidth.
3. Now we know how we can justify a line ,we need to form these lines

Algorithm
```
result=[]                //To store the justified lines
cur_line=[]             //this is store the words in current line
num_of_letters=0       // number of letters in current line  
Iterate each word in input:
	check if we add word to cur_line exceeds maxWidth:
		if it exceeds : 
			add spaces evenly to current line and add it result
			Since we are done with cur_line we empty it and set num_of_letters to 0
		add the word to cur_line                          //if the word exceeds maxWidth this word will be added to a newline beacuse we reset cur_line in previous step
		add num_of_letters with length of word
after iterating all words check if cur_line is empty      // we add line to result only when it exceeds maxWidth,but when we finish all words some words might be left in cur_line
if not empty :
	add spaces and add to result 

return result
```
Now u know approach try it, if u get stuck continue reading
* **Formula to check whether word will fit in cur_line** : `num_of_letters+len(word) + len(cur_line) > maxWidth`
	Keep in mind len(cur_line) is number of words in cur_line,so if there are two words it translates to single spaces between words after adding third word.
	Understand above statement properly,u are doing this in greedy approach words should have atleast a single space between them.
	Ex: 
	`cur_line="this",is","an"` and  word to be added `"example"` then condition will be
	num_of_letters=8, len(word)=len("example")=7,len(cur_line)=3 so 8+3+7>16 so we break the line and add "example" to next Line.
	"this is an example" >16 (adding example will make line>maxWidth)
*  **How to justify a line** :To do that we need to find number of spaces to insert so it reaches maxWidth, so `maxWidth - num_of_letters (in cur_line) ` gives it.
Say we have 4 words (u have to fill 3 spots ) and 5 spaces to add to reach maxWidth,we need to distribute evenly from left to right according to question, so (2,2,1) will be spacing between them.(Think of adding 5 stones to 3 containers from left to right one at a time ,at end how many stones are in each container?)
divide the number of spaces to add by (num of words -1) .
The Qutioent is space to be added between words.
The remainder is extra spaces we need to distribute from left to right one at a time (Think of stones 5/3=1 , 5%3=2 so first two containers will have extra one stone (1+1, 1+1, 1).
To make it simple u are adding spaces in Round robin fashion,just to do it in one step we divide and use qutieont and remainder.
**A corner case while justifying is what if that line has only word then we need to add empty spaces until it reaches maxWidth**
While justifying last line a single space between words is enough with last word appended with spaces to cover maxWidth. (Last line should be left justified according to Problem)



Code in C++
```
string fillSpaces(vector<string> line,int num_letters, int maxWidth){
        string res;
        int spaces_to_add=maxWidth-num_letters;
        int between_space=spaces_to_add/(line.size()-1);
        int extra_spaces=spaces_to_add%(line.size()-1);
        for(int i=0;i<line.size()-1;i++){
            res+=line[i] + string(between_space,' ')+ string(extra_spaces?1:0,' ');
            if(extra_spaces>0) extra_spaces--;
        }
        res+=line.back();

        return res;
    }


    vector<string> fullJustify(vector<string>& words, int maxWidth) {
        vector<string> res;
        vector<string> line;
        int cur_letters = 0;
        for(auto word:words){
            if(cur_letters + word.length() + line.size() > maxWidth){   
                if(line.size()==1){
                    res.push_back(line[0]+string(maxWidth-cur_letters,' '));  //corner case
                }
                else
                   res.push_back(fillSpaces(line,cur_letters,maxWidth)); 
                cur_letters=0;
                line.clear();

            }
            line.push_back(word);
            cur_letters+=word.length();
        }      
        string last;      //For the last line Left Justification
        for(int i=0;i<line.size()-1;i++){
            last+=line[i]+" ";

        }
        last+=line.back()+string(maxWidth-(cur_letters+line.size()-1),' ');
        res.push_back(last);
        return res;

    }
