# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The problem is really simple.It just needs some observation skills. Let us just take an example .let the column number be **126**

Now,Let us just calculate the **remainder and divisor of 126 when we divide it by 26**

**Remainder = 126%26 = 22**

**Divisor = 126/22 = 4**

Now, 22nd alphabet is "V"
Now, 4th alphabet is "D"

SO your string becomes **"DV"**

Now, let us take a bigger example , Let the no be **2832355**

Now, let us calculate the remainder and divisor 

Remainder = 2832355%26 = 19

Divisor = 2832355/26 = 108936

Now we know the 19th alphabet is "S" so we will add this in our answer string ,
Now our divisor (108936) is really big so again we will calculate the remiander and divisor for this..

Remainder = 108936%26 = 22

Divisor = 108936/26 = 4189

Now, we know the 22nd alpahbet is "V", so we will add this in our answer string so our answer string becomes "SV"

Now, 4189 is also really big, wo we will again repeat this step and keep on adding the remainder.

**We need to make sure that when the divisor is less then or equal to 26, we will add that particular alphabet in our string ...**

Now, just **reverse this string** and return the ans...

# **SPECIAL CASE-**

Let us say the no is "52", Now you see when we calculate the remiander and divisor it comes to be

rem = 52 %26 = 0

div = 52/26 = 2

Now, In such case when the rem = 0, if you follow the above case , then your answer will become "B", but that is wrong..

SO, **whenever you rem comes to be 0**, you will do **rem  =  rem +26** and **div = div-1**

so , if you calculate the string now, so it will become **"AZ"**...so this is how you will handel such cases

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
We are continously dividing the number by 26..so it will be **log(n**), but the **base of that log will be 26**...

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
**No extra space taken**

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    string convertToTitle(int col) {
        string ans = "";
        while(col>0)
        {
            int d = col/26;
            int rem = col%26;
            if(rem==0)
            {
                rem  =26;
                d--;
            }
            if(rem!=0)
            {
                char z= rem+64;
                ans+=z;
            }
            if(d<=26 && d!=0)
            {
                char z = d+64;
                ans+=z;
                reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end());
                return ans;
            }
            else
            {
                col = d;
            }
        }

        reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end());
        return ans;

    }
};
```
